metadata.description: Thrombomodulin (TM) is an endothelial cell surface receptor specific for thrombin. TM is involved in promoting activation of the anticoagulant protein C pathway during coagulation [3]. Soluble TM is the product of proteolytic degradation of endothelial-bound TM. When the endothelium is damaged, endothelial-bound TM is released from the endothelial surface, resulting in a significant increase in sTM concentration [4]. Measured using ELISA.

metadata.notes: 0 = above lower limit of detection; 1 = below lower limit of detection

metadata.additional_notes:
VL-Values 2.67-5.33 defined as 2.67 (5.33 / 2). Values below 2.67 defined as 1.89 (2.67 / square root of 2)
R plex-Values between blank and 24.4 defined as 17.25 (24.4 / square root of 2). Values below blank defined as 12.2 (24.4 / 2). Values above high standard calculated by MSD software.
S plex-Standard values do not account for 2X dilution performed prior to assay.
S plex-Values adjusted for 2X dilution. Adjusted values above low standard defined as 0.1122 (0.1587 / square root of 2). Adjusted values below low standard defined as 0.079 (0.1587 /2).
S plex-Values above high standard calculated by MSD software.
Quanterix-Standard values do not account for 4X dilution performed by machine.
Quanterix-Values below LLOD (0.09 per manufacturer) defined as 0.07 (0.09 / square root of 2).
Quanterix-Values above ULOD calculated by Quanterix software. Values beyond calculable range defined as maximum value plus 1.
Luminex-Calculated values beyond standard curve provided by Luminex software were included.
Luminex-Values below calculable range were defined as minimum calculated value divided by square root of 2.
Luminex-Values above calculable range were defined as maximum calculated value plus 1.
